{
  "title": "Working with Jenkins Plugins",
  "content": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Jenkins plugins are essential for enhancing the functionality of the Jenkins CI/CD tool. They serve as the building blocks that allow Jenkins to expand beyond its basic setup, offering over 2,000 community-contributed tools to customize your automation. </span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Plugins bridge the gap between Jenkins and the rest of your tech stack, connecting it to tools like GitHub, Docker, Slack, and AWS to create a unified workflow.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>You can easily search, install, and update plugins directly through the Jenkins Dashboard, allowing you to add complex features with just a few clicks.</span></li></ul><gfg-carousel><gfg-carousel-content alt=\"key_plugins_for_test_automation.webp\" height=\"400\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260120160604500446/key_plugins_for_test_automation.webp\" width=\"800\"></gfg-carousel-content><gfg-carousel-content alt=\"plugins_jenkins_workflows.webp\" height=\"400\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260120160604313319/plugins_jenkins_workflows.webp\" width=\"800\"></gfg-carousel-content></gfg-carousel><h2 id=\"jenkins-plugins-workflow1-test-execution-integration\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Jenkins Plugins Workflow</span></h2><h3 id=\"1-test-execution-integration\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>1. Test Execution Integration</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Integrates with tools like Selenium, Cucumber, TestNG, and JUnit.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Automatically generates and publishes test reports.</span></li></ul><h3 id=\"2-reporting\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>2. Reporting</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Provides detailed insights into test results with plugins like Allure and HTML Publisher.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Visualizes build trends, pass/fail ratios, and test execution details.</span></li></ul><h3 id=\"3-cicd-integration\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>3. CI/CD Integration</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Accelerates feedback loops.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Identifies defects early by integrating tools like Git and Maven.</span></li></ul><h3 id=\"4-notification-and-collaboration\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>4. Notification and Collaboration</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Sends automated alerts using email or communication tools like Slack and Microsoft Teams.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Accessing Plugins in Jenkins</span></li></ul><h2 id=\"how-to-install-and-manage-jenkins-plugins\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Key Plugins for Test Automation</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>The following are the key plugins used for Test Automation:</span></p><h3 id=\"1-junit-plugin\" style=\"text-align:left\"><b><strong>1. JUnit Plugin</strong></b></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Publishes test results from JUnit or other xUnit test frameworks.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Displays test reports in the Jenkins UI and tracks test pass/fail history across builds.</span></li></ul><h3 id=\"2-testng-results-plugin\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>2. TestNG Results Plugin</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Publishes and displays results for TestNG-based tests.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Includes detailed reports on passed, failed, and skipped tests.</span></li></ul><h3 id=\"3-maven-integration-plugin\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>3. Maven Integration Plugin</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Automates building and testing for Maven projects.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Manages the build lifecycle, dependencies, and report generation.</span></li></ul><h3 id=\"4-html-publisher-plugin\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>4. HTML Publisher Plugin</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Allows Jenkins to publish and display custom HTML reports, such as those generated by frameworks like Selenium or JUnit.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Useful for visualizing test automation results.</span></li></ul><h3 id=\"5-allure-report-plugin\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>5. Allure Report Plugin</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Integrates with Allure to generate detailed and visually appealing reports for various test frameworks, including JUnit, TestNG, and Selenium.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Provides insights into test execution, including duration, environment, and failure analysis.</span></li></ul><h2 id=\"manage-jenkins-plugins\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Plugin\tPurpose</span></h2><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>JUnit Plugin\tParses test results from JUnit and displays pass/fail statistics in Jenkins.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>TestNG Plugin\tIntegrates TestNG results with Jenkins, showing method-level execution statistics.</span></li><li value=\"3\"><span>Maven Integration\tSimplifies the creation of Maven-based Jenkins jobs.</span></li><li value=\"4\"><span>HTML Publisher\tPublishes HTML reports generated by automation frameworks.</span></li><li value=\"5\"><span>Allure Reports\tGenerates visually appealing and detailed test execution reports.</span></li><li value=\"6\"><span>Cucumber Reports\tPublishes JSON-based Cucumber reports in an easy-to-read HTML format.</span></li><li value=\"7\"><span>Git Plugin\tIntegrates Jenkins with Git repositories.</span></li><li value=\"8\"><span>Email Extension\tSends email notifications based on test results or build statuses.</span></li></ul><h2 id=\"how-to-use-jenkins-plugins-stepbystep-guides\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>How to Use Jenkins Plugins</span></h2><blockquote><p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Publishing Cucumber Reports</strong></b></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Objective: </strong></b><span>Generate a readable report from Cucumber's JSON output.</span></p></blockquote><h3 id=\"install-the-cucumber-reports-plugin\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 1: Install the Cucumber Reports Plugin</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Install Cucumber Reports Plugin:</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Navigate to Available Plugins and search for \"Cucumber Reports.\"</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt='Available Plugins and search for \"Cucumber Reports.\"' height=\"284\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125160103379762/Screenshot-2024-11-25-160107.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125160103379762/Screenshot-2024-11-25-160107.jpg 744w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125160103379762/Screenshot-2024-11-25-160107-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125160103379762/Screenshot-2024-11-25-160107-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125160103379762/Screenshot-2024-11-25-160107-300.jpg 300w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125160103379762/Screenshot-2024-11-25-160107-660.jpg 660w\" width=\"744\"/><figcaption>Available Plugins and search for \"Cucumber Reports.\"</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Install the plugin.</span></li></ul><h3 id=\"configure-jenkins-job\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 2: Configure Jenkins Job</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Firstly check the cucumber project run locally as expected</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Screenshot-2024-11-25-160828\" height=\"529\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125161348541381/Screenshot-2024-11-25-160828.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125161348541381/Screenshot-2024-11-25-160828.jpg 569w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125161348541381/Screenshot-2024-11-25-160828-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125161348541381/Screenshot-2024-11-25-160828-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125161348541381/Screenshot-2024-11-25-160828-300.jpg 300w\" width=\"569\"/><figcaption>cucumber project run locally</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Add a build step to execute your Cucumber project.</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"build step to execute your Cucumber project.\" height=\"284\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162218986987/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162223.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162218986987/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162223.jpg 879w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162218986987/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162223-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162218986987/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162223-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162218986987/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162223-300.jpg 300w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162218986987/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162223-660.jpg 660w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162218986987/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162223-768.jpg 768w\" width=\"879\"/><figcaption>build step to execute your Cucumber project.</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Copy the project from existing project which you are already created:</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Copy the project from existing project\" height=\"267\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162327994316/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162330.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162327994316/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162330.jpg 466w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162327994316/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162330-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162327994316/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162330-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162327994316/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162330-300.jpg 300w\" width=\"466\"/><figcaption>Copy the project from existing project</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Updates the goal as per our requirement:</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Updates the goal as per our requiremen\" height=\"213\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162527328450/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162532.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162527328450/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162532.jpg 436w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162527328450/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162532-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162527328450/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162532-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162527328450/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162532-300.jpg 300w\" width=\"436\"/><figcaption>Updates the goal as per our requiremen</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Ensure the test runner generates a cucumber.json file.</span></li></ul><h3 id=\"postbuild-actions\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 3: Post-Build Actions</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Select Cucumber Reports.</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Select Cucumber Reports\" height=\"551\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162627503790/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162631.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162627503790/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162631.jpg 484w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162627503790/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162631-100.jpg 88w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162627503790/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162631-200.jpg 176w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162627503790/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162631-300.jpg 264w\" width=\"484\"/><figcaption>Select Cucumber Reports</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>After that save the project and build the project.</span></li></ul><h3 id=\"run-the-job\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 4: Run the Job</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>View the generated report in the Jenkins dashboard.</span></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><b><strong>Output</strong></b></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>A detailed HTML report showing:</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Passed, failed, and skipped steps.</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"generated report in the Jenkins dashboard\" height=\"546\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125163155408698/Screenshot-2024-11-25-163046.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125163155408698/Screenshot-2024-11-25-163046.jpg 873w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125163155408698/Screenshot-2024-11-25-163046-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125163155408698/Screenshot-2024-11-25-163046-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125163155408698/Screenshot-2024-11-25-163046-300.jpg 300w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125163155408698/Screenshot-2024-11-25-163046-660.jpg 660w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125163155408698/Screenshot-2024-11-25-163046-768.jpg 768w\" width=\"873\"/><figcaption>generated report in the Jenkins dashboard</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Execution time for each step.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Overall test summary.</span></li></ul><h2 id=\"integrating-jenkins-with-testng\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Integrating jenkins with TestNG</span></h2><blockquote><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Objective: Visualize TestNG execution results in Jenkins.</span></p></blockquote><h3 id=\"steps\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 1: Install TestNG Results Plugin:</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Search for \"TestNG Results\" in Available Plugins and install it.</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"TestNG Results plugin\" height=\"309\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164009306617/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164013.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164009306617/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164013.jpg 450w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164009306617/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164013-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164009306617/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164013-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164009306617/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164013-300.jpg 300w\" width=\"450\"/><figcaption>TestNG Results plugin</figcaption></figure><h3 id=\"configure-job\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 2: Configure Job</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Execute TestNG tests and ensure the results are saved in XML format in locally first</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Configure Job\" height=\"538\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164346198037/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164348.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164346198037/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164348.jpg 600w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164346198037/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164348-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164346198037/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164348-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164346198037/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164348-300.jpg 300w\" width=\"600\"/><figcaption>Configure Job</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Create a new project in jenkins.</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"create a new testng job in jenkins\" height=\"264\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164607282730/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164603.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164607282730/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164603.jpg 763w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164607282730/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164603-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164607282730/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164603-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164607282730/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164603-300.jpg 300w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125164607282730/Screenshot-2024-11-25-164603-660.jpg 660w\" width=\"763\"/><figcaption>create a new testng job in jenkins</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Use the same as last we used copy the project using the last project configuration which we used.</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"copy the project using the last project\" height=\"267\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162327994316/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162330.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162327994316/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162330.jpg 466w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162327994316/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162330-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162327994316/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162330-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125162327994316/Screenshot-2024-11-25-162330-300.jpg 300w\" width=\"466\"/><figcaption>copy the project using the last project</figcaption></figure><blockquote><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Use this Repository URL for the Project: </span><a href=\"https://github.com/rakesh-vardan/Learn_TA_CucumberBDD\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Repository</span></a></p></blockquote><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Update the Repository URL in the Jenkins project configuration</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Update the Repository URL\" height=\"430\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125165507549598/Screenshot-2024-11-25-165512.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125165507549598/Screenshot-2024-11-25-165512.jpg 709w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125165507549598/Screenshot-2024-11-25-165512-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125165507549598/Screenshot-2024-11-25-165512-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125165507549598/Screenshot-2024-11-25-165512-300.jpg 300w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125165507549598/Screenshot-2024-11-25-165512-660.jpg 660w\" width=\"709\"/><figcaption>Update the Repository URL</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>The goals and options of the project is like these:</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"The goals\" height=\"459\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125170105670987/Screenshot-2024-11-25-170109.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125170105670987/Screenshot-2024-11-25-170109.jpg 529w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125170105670987/Screenshot-2024-11-25-170109-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125170105670987/Screenshot-2024-11-25-170109-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125170105670987/Screenshot-2024-11-25-170109-300.jpg 300w\" width=\"529\"/><figcaption>The goals</figcaption></figure><h3 id=\"postbuild-action\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 3: Post-Build Action</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Select Publish </span><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/software-testing/testng-tutorial/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>TestNG</span></a><span> Results.</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Select Publish TestNG Results\" height=\"559\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125170605477650/Screenshot-2024-11-25-170607.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125170605477650/Screenshot-2024-11-25-170607.jpg 578w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125170605477650/Screenshot-2024-11-25-170607-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125170605477650/Screenshot-2024-11-25-170607-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125170605477650/Screenshot-2024-11-25-170607-300.jpg 300w\" width=\"578\"/><figcaption>Select Publish TestNG Results</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Provide the path to the TestNG results file.</span></li></ul><h3 id=\"run-job\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 4: Run Job</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>View method-level statistics and overall execution details.</span></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><b><strong>Output:</strong></b></p><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Run Job\" height=\"577\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125171039641644/Screenshot-2024-11-25-171040.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125171039641644/Screenshot-2024-11-25-171040.jpg 869w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125171039641644/Screenshot-2024-11-25-171040-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125171039641644/Screenshot-2024-11-25-171040-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125171039641644/Screenshot-2024-11-25-171040-300.jpg 300w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125171039641644/Screenshot-2024-11-25-171040-660.jpg 660w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125171039641644/Screenshot-2024-11-25-171040-768.jpg 768w\" width=\"869\"/><figcaption>Run Job</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Execution trends and test statuses displayed in Jenkins.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Here are the testNG results :</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\" testNG results\" height=\"516\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125171238237853/Screenshot-2024-11-25-171239.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125171238237853/Screenshot-2024-11-25-171239.jpg 1009w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125171238237853/Screenshot-2024-11-25-171239-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125171238237853/Screenshot-2024-11-25-171239-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125171238237853/Screenshot-2024-11-25-171239-300.jpg 300w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125171238237853/Screenshot-2024-11-25-171239-660.jpg 660w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125171238237853/Screenshot-2024-11-25-171239-768.jpg 768w\" width=\"1009\"/><figcaption> testNG results</figcaption></figure><h2 id=\"3-publishing-html-reports\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>3. Publishing HTML Reports</span></h2><blockquote><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Objective: Display custom HTML reports generated by automation frameworks.</span></p></blockquote><h3 id=\"steps-1\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 1: Install HTML Publisher Plugin:</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Search for \"HTML Publisher\" and install the plugin.</span></li></ul><h3 id=\"configure-job-1\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 2: Configure Job</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Create a new job</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Create a new job\" height=\"469\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125173338080241/Screenshot-2024-11-25-173342.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125173338080241/Screenshot-2024-11-25-173342.jpg 824w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125173338080241/Screenshot-2024-11-25-173342-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125173338080241/Screenshot-2024-11-25-173342-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125173338080241/Screenshot-2024-11-25-173342-300.jpg 300w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125173338080241/Screenshot-2024-11-25-173342-660.jpg 660w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125173338080241/Screenshot-2024-11-25-173342-768.jpg 768w\" width=\"824\"/><figcaption>Create a new job</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Copy the same project which we last used:</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Copy the same project\" height=\"127\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125175819010593/Screenshot-2024-11-25-175822.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125175819010593/Screenshot-2024-11-25-175822.jpg 518w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125175819010593/Screenshot-2024-11-25-175822-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125175819010593/Screenshot-2024-11-25-175822-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125175819010593/Screenshot-2024-11-25-175822-300.jpg 300w\" width=\"518\"/><figcaption>Copy the same project</figcaption></figure><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>We used all configuration of the last project only we change the report template with the HTML publisher:</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Select Publish HTML Reports.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Provide the directory and file path.</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"report template with the HTML publisher\" height=\"498\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180114209503/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180119.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180114209503/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180119.jpg 439w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180114209503/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180119-100.jpg 88w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180114209503/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180119-200.jpg 176w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180114209503/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180119-300.jpg 264w\" width=\"439\"/><figcaption>report template with the HTML publisher</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Ensure your automation framework generates an </span><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/html/html-introduction/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>HTML</span></a><span> report.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><span>Specify the report directory and file name (e.g., </span><b><strong>target/surefire-reports/index.html</strong></b><span>).</span></li></ul><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Specify the report directory and file name \" height=\"536\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180417032073/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180421.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180417032073/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180421.jpg 527w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180417032073/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180421-100.jpg 98w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180417032073/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180421-200.jpg 197w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180417032073/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180421-300.jpg 295w\" width=\"527\"/><figcaption>Specify the report directory and file name </figcaption></figure><h3 id=\"run-job-1\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Step 3: Run Job</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Access the HTML report from the Jenkins dashboard.</span></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><b><strong>Output</strong></b></p><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Access the HTML report\" height=\"350\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180804177607/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180807.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180804177607/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180807.jpg 617w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180804177607/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180807-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180804177607/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180807-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241125180804177607/Screenshot-2024-11-25-180807-300.jpg 300w\" width=\"617\"/><figcaption>Access the HTML report</figcaption></figure><ul><li value=\"1\"><span>Fully formatted HTML reports, accessible via Jenkins.</span></li></ul>",
